@Node "Overview" "ConfUMS.guide/Overview"
@Toc "Main"

Overview
********

   What is ConfUMS?

   ConfUMS uses the internal functions of the ums.library for editing
the @{b}ums.config@{ub}. This is done so transparently that once you have
started using ConfUMS, you may never take a look at your @{b}ums.config@{ub}
again. Well, okay, user-, alias- and netgroups-maintenance is not
possible right now, but will be added soon.

   ConfUMS v1.1a will remain the last release to support old v10 of
UMS-Server. ConfUMS v1.2 requires at least v11 to run as its vastly
enhanced functionability arises directly from improvement of the
UMS-Server. A public beta version of UMS v11 has recently been released,
bringing as powerful innovations as:

   @{b}*@{ub} full control over server variables, i.e. Read- and WriteAccess,
     Options, Aka etc.

   @{b}*@{ub} variable locking: a secure way to prevent two users from editing
     the same variable at the same time in a network environment.

   @{b}*@{ub} config-modification "on the net" - you may edit your personal
     configuration in an Envoy network environment without actually
     knowing where the @{b}ums.config@{ub} hides.

   In a local environment ConfUMS offers many functions to comfortably
modify your UMS configuration. Three editors are available: for
single-line variables, variables that consist of multiple lines and so
called "listkind" variables e.g. the expire.grouplist.

   As stated above more v11 features will be supported in the future,
but only if I get some feedback from ConfUMS users! @{i}Simply write me a
mail!@{ui}


@EndNode

