@Node "Entrygroup" "ConfUMS.guide/Entrygroup"
@Toc "Mainwindow"

The entrygroup
==============

   The buttons in this group are only available if you have selected an
entry in the list of variables, See @{"Variables" Link "Variables"}.

   If you did so, you can


 @{" delete " Link "Delete"}                   to remove variables from the configuration

 @{" clone " Link "Clone"}                    to clone the contents of one variable into another

 @{" rename " Link "Rename"}                   to rename a variable

 @{" make local " Link "Make local"}               to make a global variable a local one

 @{" make global " Link "Make global"}              to make a local variable a global one


@EndNode

@Node "Delete" "ConfUMS.guide/Delete"
@Next "Clone"
@Toc "Entrygroup"

@{b}Delete@{ub} button
-------------

@{i}Button@{ui}
     Delete

@{i}Function@{ui}
     Remove the entry highlighted in the variable listview from the
     @{b}ums.config@{ub}. Depending on the value you entered in
     ConfUMS.ForceDelete a requester will pop up asking you to confirm
     deletion of that var.

@{i}Shortcut@{ui}
     D

@{i}See also@{ui}
@{"ConfUMS.ForceDelete" Link "ConfUMS.ForceDelete"}.


@EndNode

