@Node "FAQ" "ConfUMS.guide/FAQ"
@Toc "Main"

FAQ - Frequently Asked Questions
********************************

   This section contains questions which users often asked me, so if
you have a question concerning ConfUMS, please consult this section
before mailing me.

@{i}Why does ConfUMS not offer Save/Use/Cancel like a Prefs program?@{ui}
     Sorry, ConfUMS' icon may be a little confusing. ConfUMS isn't
     meant to be a Prefs-program for UMS (like those in @{b}sys:Prefs/@{ub}).
     The concept for a prefs-like program would have been much more
     complicated: every change to a variable must be buffered until the
     users leaves ConfUMS with the Save function. And even a
     Use-functionality would not be possible, because UMS itself does
     not support such a concept. So please consider ConfUMS as a
     config-@{i}editor@{ui} not as a prefs-program - it's ConfUMS, not
     UMSPrefs!

@{i}ConfUMS kills the comments in my @{b}ums.config@{ub} and sorts it!@{ui}
     Wrong! ConfUMS does not even know about a - what do you call it? -
     @{b}ums.config@{ub}. ;-)

     ConfUMS just communicates with the @{b}ums.library@{ub}, the actual changes
     to your @{b}ums.config@{ub} are performed by the UMS-server itself!
     ConfUMS exerts @{i}no@{ui} influence on how your @{b}ums.config@{ub} is going to be
     written and what it looks like! Nevertheless with UMS v11 you can
     put @{b}SAVECOMMENTS@{ub} into the global server variable @{b}Options@{ub} and UMS
     will not kill your comments any more.

   To be continued...


@EndNode

@Node "History" "ConfUMS.guide/History"
@Toc "Main"

History
*******

   @{i}v1.2 (24.12.94)@{ui}

   @{b}*@{ub} ConfUMS requires a minimum of UMS v11 and MUI v2.2 to run. UMS v10
     is not supported any longer!

   @{b}*@{ub} the error-handling has been greatly improved: if a config variable
     cannot be written to ums.config e.g. due to a locked config,
     ConfUMS lets you try again instead of jumping back to the
     main-window.

   @{b}*@{ub} employs memory pools, thus reduces fragmentation of main memory.

   @{b}*@{ub} now really respects the login-guide as described in ums.doc

   @{b}*@{ub} relogin-function: change the user logged into ConfUMS without
     restarting it. (as requested by Tron on the UMS meeting)

   @{b}*@{ub} when changing the password, you now have two stringgadgets to
     enter the new one. Both string have to match otherwise the
     password will not be changed. (requested by Mario Kemper)

   @{b}*@{ub} the multiline editor now lets you re-edit a variable by using the
     "Start-Editor" button, accompanied by the config var
     ConfUMS.MLStartEditor.

   @{b}*@{ub} it's now possible to run two ConfUMSes on one machine, e.g. on
     different message bases or for different users.

   @{b}*@{ub} the contents of the preview window can be shown in UMS' quoted
     format.

   @{b}*@{ub} many "cosmetic" changes, let's call this the "Ellen Betrix
     Release" (hi Golle :-)

   @{i}v1.1a (21.07.94)@{ui}

   @{b}*@{ub} fixed a bad bug that let ConfUMS crash when starting from CLI
     (reported by hartmut Goebel)

   @{i}v1.1 (20.07.94)@{ui}

   @{b}*@{ub} ConfUMS now features localization as of AmigaOS v2.1+

   @{b}*@{ub} new configvars: ConfUMS.CallListkind, ConfUMS.Stack (last one as
     requested by Oliver Rummeyer)

   @{b}*@{ub} fixed a bug in the listkind-editor that let ConfUMS crash with
     some entries (reported by Alexander Bauer).

   @{b}*@{ub} some "cosmetic" changes

   @{i}v1.0 (16.06.94)@{ui}

   @{b}*@{ub} first public release.


@EndNode

@Node "Future" "ConfUMS.guide/Future"
@Toc "Main"

Future
******

   The following features are on my todo-list for future ConfUMS
releases:

   @{b}*@{ub} support for more UMS v11 features i.e. quoting and creation of
     users, aliases, netgroups etc.

   @{b}*@{ub} german docs

   @{b}*@{ub} to be continued...


@EndNode

@Node "MUI" "ConfUMS.guide/MUI"
@Toc "Main"

MUI
***

                         This application uses

                       MUI - MagicUserInterface

                (c) Copyright 1993/94 by Stefan Stuntz

   MUI is a system to generate and maintain graphical user interfaces.
With the  aid  of  a  preferences program, the user of an application
has the ability to customize the outfit according to his personal taste.

   MUI is distributed as shareware. To obtain a complete package
containing lots of examples and more information about registration
please look for a  file  called  "muiXXusr.lha"  (XX means the latest
version number) on your local bulletin boards or on public domain disks.

          If you want to register directly, feel free to send

                         DM 30.-  or  US$ 20.-

                                  to

                             Stefan Stuntz

                       Eduard-Spranger-Straße 7

                             80935 München

                                GERMANY


